rom the Hooker-line Connecticut center."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Presumed daughter's line reconverged Hooker branches","body":"Through Laura E. Hooker Shader — Myron's presumed daughter by first wife Sally Brooks — the line runs forward to Caroline E. Shader who married Thomas Harvey Hooker, descendant of Myron's half-brother Thomas Gould Hooker. That third-cousin marriage between two branches of Captain Thomas Hooker's descendants reconverged a line that had split four generations earlier. Their child Charles Theodore Hooker qualifies as double Hooker ancestry."}],"cross_connections":[],"burial":{"plot_notes":"Greenwood Cemetery, Kendall, Orleans County NY (per WikiTree). Cemetery not yet built as separate CEM entry."},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"myron-hooker-1788"},"H02436":{"id":"H02436","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"is_easter_egg":false,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":8},"bio":{"first_name":"Betsey","last_name":"Bacon","maiden_name":"Hooker","married_names":["Bacon"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Betsey Hooker Bacon"},"birth":{"year":1839,"country":"United States","historical_notes":"EH 2436 says b.1839, but Myron's wife Sally Brooks would have been advanced age in 1839 (sons Myron Smith b.1820, Thomas Cullen b.1822). EH date may be in error; further research warranted."},"death":{"year":1839,"note":"EH 2436 says \"She died 1839\" — same year as her recorded birth. Likely either an EH error in birth year (perhaps 1819?), or she died very young. If died in infancy, would qualify for died_in_infancy tag. Source ambiguous."},"parents":{"father_id":"H01272","mother_id":"X02277"},"nu